From: Gilly <gilroyscott1970@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] thermal: airoha: fix low-trip clamp using wrong variable

In airoha_thermal_set_trips(), the low-trip branch clamps 'high' into
'low': low = clamp_t(int, high, ...). It must clamp 'low', otherwise the
low trip threshold is derived from the high temperature.

Scope note (2026-06-20): this used to also fix the TEMPOFFSETL regmap_write
(TEMP_TO_RAW(priv, high) -> low), but the base 402-01-...regmap-API.patch
already writes 'low' there (and upstream commit 71d0568 fixes the same line
for trees that still had 'high'). Bundling both in one hunk caused GNU patch
to treat the whole hunk as already-applied and silently skip the clamp fix.
Reduced to the clamp line only so it actually lands.
---
--- a/drivers/thermal/airoha_thermal.c
+++ b/drivers/thermal/airoha_thermal.c
@@ -373,7 +373,7 @@
 
 	if (low != -INT_MAX) {
 		/* Validate low and clamp it to a supported value */
-		low = clamp_t(int, high, RAW_TO_TEMP(priv, 0),
+		low = clamp_t(int, low, RAW_TO_TEMP(priv, 0),
 			      RAW_TO_TEMP(priv, FIELD_MAX(EN7581_DOUT_TADC_MASK)));
 
 		/* We offset the low temp of 1°C to trigger correct event */
